Operating system:
    Operating system is a software program which enables the computer hardware to communicate and operate with the computer software/application programs.
Kernal:
    Kernal is critical part of operating system, It works as intermediatory b/w compurter hardware and OS.It manages the computer resources like schedulling cpu, allocating memory, device i/o, system efficiency and stability.
Shell:
    Shell is OS user inetrface and interpretor of commands, it passes the commands gives by the user to Kernal and returns the output of the commands.